Distribution. This species is restricted to the temperate grassland, semidesert and desert steppe vegetation of Mongolia and the neighbouring areas of southern Siberia, eastern Kazakhstan , and northern China ; a distribution map was presented by Putshkov (1986: 98, fig. 54) . Its distribution in China can be summarized as follows: Inner Mongolia : Alxa League!, Xilingol League!, Ar Horqin Banner!, several additional localities ( Hsiao 1977 ; Liu & Nonnaizab 1985 ; Nonnaizab 1986 , 1999 ;
Ma et al. 1991
); Qinghai : Qilian!; Ningxia : W foot of Mt. Helan, Khar- Us [Lake] ( Zheng & Gao 1990 ); Shanxi : Linfen, Yuncheng (
Li et al. 2007
); the records from Ningxia and Shanxi could not be verified. The record from Daxing’anling Prefecture, Heilongjiang ( Hsiao 1977 ), is erroneous, and pertains to
M. miriformis gracilis
; Hua (2000) listed it from Sichuan and Xinjiang , but these data are based on unknown sources therefore they are suspicious.
